{"type":"compaction","id":"f5e85c8b","parentId":"226f9a3f","timestamp":"2026-04-23T03:15:11.129Z","summary":"## Goal\n1. Create professional Confluence documentation for project **AHV QLHV** based on the actual codebase, not copied templates.\n2. Include **user stories**, **pain points**, and **detailed database/model attribute documentation** suitable for adding ERD images later.\n3. Rework docs to match the **writing style/format of AHV Work** and eventually turn that style into a reusable **agent/spec** for future projects.\n4. Separately, start the **SafeSight AI / safety** project and expose it publicly for external access.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- User explicitly said: write for **`ahv-qlhv`**, not CMS Teacher, and **do not copy** reference/template content.\n- Must base docs on the real repos:\n  - FE: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe`\n  - BE: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be`\n- Documentation should be **accurate, professional, detailed**.\n- Must include:\n  - **User Stories**\n  - **Pain Points**\n  - **Bảng thuộc tính của từng model** in Database/ERD section\n- User will later add ERD images manually.\n- Confluence markdown rendering looked bad; docs should be created in **Confluence-ready/HTML-ish clean format**.\n- Need to **clean up/avoid confusion with old mistakenly created CMS Teacher pages**.\n- User wants future docs to follow **AHV Work** style; need to study that format carefully and convert it into a reusable **agent/spec**.\n- User later requested: **pull latest code from `develop`** for both FE/BE before expanding Database Document.\n- For safety app: user needs **public access from outside VPS**.\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Initially checked `HEARTBEAT.md`; responded `HEARTBEAT_OK`.\n- [x] Confirmed wrong initial direction and switched from CMS Teacher to **AHV QLHV** after user correction.\n- [x] Located and inspected real repos:\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be`\n- [x] Inspected FE/BE package/readme and backend schemas/models including:\n  - `student.model.ts`\n  - `course.model.ts`\n  - `course_student.model.ts`\n  - `user.model.ts`\n  - `payment.model.ts`\n  - `exam_batch.model.ts`\n  - `exam.model.ts`\n  - `lesson.model.ts`\n  - `dat_session.model.ts`\n  - `license_category.model.ts`\n  - `stadium.model.ts`\n  - `settings.model.ts`\n  - `support_request.model.ts`\n  - `notification.model.ts`\n  - `announcement.model.ts`\n  - `city.model.ts`\n  - `src/interface/docs/swagger.json`\n- [x] Created new Confluence docs for AHV QLHV in space `AHVTEACHER`:\n  - `130940930` — **AHV QLHV - Project Overview**\n  - `130777282` — **AHV QLHV - Business Analysis (Pain Points & User Stories)**\n  - `130744553` — **AHV QLHV - Database Documentation & Model Attributes**\n- [x] Because old pages rendered as raw markdown and `update_page` often failed with `Confluence error 400`, created “clean” Confluence-rendered pages instead:\n  - `130940947` — **AHV QLHV - Project Overview (Clean)**\n  - `130810441` — **AHV QLHV - Business Analysis (Clean)**\n  - `130777301` — **AHV QLHV - Database Documentation (Clean)**\n  - `130777316` — **AHV QLHV - System Architecture (Clean)**\n  - `130777331` — **AHV QLHV - Technical Documentation (Clean)**\n  - `130940964` — **AHV QLHV - API Documentation (Clean)**\n- [x] Pulled latest code from `develop`:\n  - FE repo pulled while on branch `fix/sat-hach-map-error`, updated to `origin/develop` fast-forward `0dfa36d..815c670`\n  - BE repo on branch `develop`, updated `a7f4c6f..4ff139c`\n- [x] After pull, created a more detailed database doc:\n  - `130940979` — **AHV QLHV - Database Documentation (Detailed)**\n- [x] Started safety project:\n  - Found project at `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/safesight-ai/frontend`\n  - Started dev server on `http://localhost:3001`\n- [x] Exposed safety project publicly via Cloudflare tunnel:\n  - Public URL: `https://introductory-government-imagination-sept.trycloudflare.com`\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Study **AHV Work** Confluence documentation format closely and derive a reusable **documentation-writing agent/spec**.\n- [ ] Rewrite/align AHV QLHV docs to match **AHV Work** style once sample pages can be accessed.\n- [ ] Clean up / mark obsolete the old wrong CMS Teacher pages to avoid confusion.\n- [ ] Potentially further expand Database Documentation with indexes, collection names, enum values, validation rules, soft delete/timestamp strategy.\n\n### Blocked\n- Confluence space **AW (AHV Work)** could not be reliably explored:\n  - `confluence__search_pages(query=\"Project Overview\", space_key=\"AW\")` returned `[]`\n  - Some searches returned `Error: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'key')`\n- Browser access to Confluence was unavailable:\n  - `browser(action=\"open\", target=\"host\", url=\"https://dtlx.atlassian.net/spaces/AW\")`\n  - Error: `No supported browser found (Chrome/Brave/Edge/Chromium on macOS, Linux, or Windows).`\n- Updating existing Confluence pages often failed:\n  - `Confluence error 400`\n- Old wrong pages were not deleted because available Confluence tools lacked direct delete support.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Switch from CMS Teacher to AHV QLHV**: User clarified the correct project is `ahv-qlhv`, based on repos in `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/`.\n- **Base docs on real codebase, not template/generalized assumptions**: To satisfy user’s requirement for accuracy and professionalism.\n- **Create new “clean” Confluence pages instead of patching markdown-heavy pages**: Because old pages rendered poorly and `update_page` often failed with `Confluence error 400`.\n- **Center database/business documentation around `CourseStudents`**: Based on actual schema, this is the core enrollment entity tying together progress, payments, lessons, DAT, and exams.\n- **Pull latest `develop` before expanding DB docs**: User explicitly requested latest code before continuing Database Documentation.\n- **Use Cloudflare quick tunnel for safety app public access**: Fastest way to expose internal VPS service externally.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Obtain access to at least 1–3 **AHV Work** Confluence sample pages (via exact title, page ID, or link) since AW search is failing.\n2. Analyze AHV Work format deeply and extract:\n   - heading structure\n   - table patterns\n   - voice/tone\n   - level of detail\n   - business/technical/database writing conventions\n3. Write a reusable **agent/spec** for documentation authoring based on AHV Work style.\n4. Rewrite/refine AHV QLHV pages to match that spec, prioritizing:\n   - `Database Documentation (Detailed)`\n   - Project Overview\n   - Business Analysis\n   - Architecture / Technical / API\n5. Clean up old mistaken pages by marking them clearly obsolete if delete is still unavailable.\n6. If asked, verify the safety public URL and keep the tunnel/dev server alive.\n\n## Critical Context\n- Correct AHV QLHV repos:\n  - FE: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe`\n  - BE: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be`\n- Important backend paths inspected:\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/student.model.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/course.model.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/course_student.model.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/user.model.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/payment.model.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/exam_batch.model.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/exam.model.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/lesson.model.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/dat_session.model.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/license_category.model.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/stadium.model.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/settings.model.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/support_request.model.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/notification.model.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/announcement.model.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/city.model.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/interface/docs/swagger.json`\n- Also inspected:\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/models/db.md`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/domain/entities/settings.entity.ts`\n  - `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/repositories/payment.repository.ts`\n- Notable read errors:\n  - `ENOENT: no such file or directory, access '/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/repositories/student.repository.ts'`\n  - `ENOENT: no such file or directory, access '/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be/src/infrastructure/database/repositories/course.repository.ts'`\n- Confluence pages created for AHV QLHV:\n  - `130940930` Project Overview\n  - `130777282` Business Analysis\n  - `130744553` Database Documentation & Model Attributes\n  - `130940947` Project Overview (Clean)\n  - `130810441` Business Analysis (Clean)\n  - `130777301` Database Documentation (Clean)\n  - `130777316`