{"type":"message","id":"b9b881eb","parentId":"b694feb0","timestamp":"2026-04-23T04:46:54.117Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mình đã bóc xong **inventory lớp 1** của hệ agent. Kết quả rõ nhất lúc này là: hệ hiện tại có một mix giữa **agent generic dùng chung** và **agent chuyên biệt cho AHV DTLX**, nhưng mức độ chuẩn hóa giữa các agent đang không đồng đều — đây sẽ là điểm mình đưa thẳng vào phần gap analysis và governance."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3WCsGWHvfVl0kRMuYwV09RH8","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/docs/multi-agent-governance-plan.md","content":"# Multi-Agent Ecosystem Documentation Plan\n\n## Scope\nBuild a full, Confluence-ready documentation set for the current multi-agent ecosystem, including:\n- inventory and taxonomy\n- architecture and orchestration model\n- standard workflows\n- agent specification framework\n- governance and escalation rules\n- metrics and adoption measurement\n- gap analysis and roadmap\n- applied case studies\n\n## Current inventory snapshot\n\n### Observed ecosystem shape\nThe current ecosystem is composed of two overlapping layers:\n\n1. **Generic reusable agents**\n   - prompt-optimizer\n   - planner\n   - senior-frontend\n   - senior-backend\n   - senior-qa\n   - senior-architect\n   - senior-security\n   - code-reviewer\n   - clean-code\n   - database-reviewer\n   - database-schema-designer\n   - content-engine\n   - content-strategy\n   - market-intelligence\n   - performance-optimizer\n   - documentation-lookup\n   - playwright-pro\n   - shadcn-expert\n   - ui-design-system\n   - ui-ux-pro-max\n   - others in the general capability layer\n\n2. **AHV DTLX domain-specific agents**\n   - ahv-dtlx-architect\n   - ahv-dtlx-agile\n   - ahv-dtlx-be\n   - ahv-dtlx-fe\n   - ahv-dtlx-qa\n   - ahv-dtlx-review\n   - ahv-dtlx-devops\n   - ahv-dtlx-db-schema\n   - ahv-dtlx-security\n   - ahv-dtlx-senior-security\n   - ahv-dtlx-ui-design\n   - ahv-dtlx-ui-ux\n   - ahv-dtlx-perf\n   - ahv-dtlx-prompt\n   - ahv-dtlx-harness\n   - ahv-dtlx-docs\n   - ahv-dtlx-epic\n   - ahv-dtlx-product-strategy\n   - ahv-dtlx-content-engine\n   - ahv-dtlx-content-strategy\n   - ahv-dtlx-market\n   - ahv-dtlx-standards\n   - ahv-dtlx-shadcn\n   - ahv-dtlx-stitch\n   - ahv-dtlx-playwright\n   - ahv-dtlx-seo\n   - and adjacent ecosystem-specific variants\n\n3. **Control layer**\n   - master-orchestrator\n   - prompt-optimizer (used as a workflow gate)\n   - potentially planner / harness-optimizer depending on task class\n\n## Initial findings\n\n### Strengths\n- Broad capability coverage already exists across product, engineering, QA, security, design, content, research, and operations.\n- There is evidence of orchestrated specialization rather than a single generalist agent.\n- Domain-specific variants for AHV DTLX indicate an intention to create reusable project-centered operational lanes.\n\n### Structural issues already visible\n- **Uneven documentation quality**: some agents have detailed role/output/workspace definitions; many others still use the generic bootstrap template.\n- **Taxonomy ambiguity**: generic and project-specific agents coexist, but there is no formal classification model.\n- **Role overlap**: multiple agents cover similar areas without a clearly documented delegation boundary.\n- **Workflow ambiguity**: orchestration intent exists, but standard agent-to-agent handoff contracts are not yet documented.\n- **Governance gap**: there is no single authoritative policy for spawn rules, escalation, quality gates, or approval boundaries per agent class.\n- **Measurement gap**: performance and adoption metrics are implied, but no formal measurement framework is documented.\n\n## Working document set to produce\n\n1. `01-multi-agent-overview.md`\n2. `02-agent-taxonomy-and-inventory.md`\n3. `03-orchestration-architecture.md`\n4. `04-standard-workflows.md`\n5. `05-agent-spec-framework.md`\n6. `06-governance-and-operating-model.md`\n7. `07-metrics-kpis-and-adoption.md`\n8. `08-gap-analysis-and-roadmap.md`\n9. `09-case-studies.md`\n\n## Draft documentation sequence\n\n### Phase 1 — Architecture foundation\n- inventory all agents\n- classify by layer: control / reusable / domain / temporary\n- define orchestration model\n- define role boundaries and overlaps\n\n### Phase 2 — Operating model\n- define standard workflows\n- define handoff contracts\n- define agent spec template\n- define governance, escalation, and safety rules\n\n### Phase 3 — Measurement and maturity\n- define KPIs and reporting layer\n- define case study structure\n- define maturity model and roadmap\n\n### Phase 4 — Publishing prep\n- convert documents to Confluence-ready structure\n- normalize heading hierarchy\n- prepare summary + appendix split for management vs technical audience\n\n## Immediate next deliverables\n- full inventory with taxonomy\n- architecture narrative\n- workflow matrix\n- gap analysis table\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":26579,"output":1263,"cacheRead":78208,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":106050,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776919588362,"responseId":"1776919590037"}}
