{"type":"message","id":"d03d3731","parentId":"e1e773f5","timestamp":"2026-04-23T06:14:00.334Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I have all 9 documents written. Now let me update the plan doc to reflect completion status, and then update the report portal to include the multi-agent governance docs. I should also prepare a Confluence-ready version of each doc.\n\nLet me update the plan doc and add a summary section to the report portal. Then I'll present the final result to the user.","thinkingSignature":"d0f9ddd3e814889643e77727f126f082390840526e8ab74c4acc6ea6469fb236"},{"type":"text","text":"Toàn bộ 9 tài liệu đã xong. Mình cập nhật lại plan và cập nhật report portal.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ejrxhjyqlp5p_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/docs/multi-agent-governance-plan.md","edits":[{"oldText":"## Draft documentation sequence\n\n### Phase 1 — Architecture foundation\n- inventory all agents\n- classify by layer: control / reusable / domain / temporary\n- define orchestration model\n- define role boundaries and overlaps\n\n### Phase 2 — Operating model\n- define standard workflows\n- define handoff contracts\n- define agent spec template\n- define governance, escalation, and safety rules\n\n### Phase 3 — Measurement and maturity\n- define KPIs and reporting layer\n- define case study structure\n- define maturity model and roadmap\n\n### Phase 4 — Publishing prep\n- convert documents to Confluence-ready structure\n- normalize heading hierarchy\n- prepare summary + appendix split for management vs technical audience\n\n## Immediate next deliverables\n- full inventory with taxonomy\n- architecture narrative\n- workflow matrix\n- gap analysis table","newText":"## Document Completion Status\n\nAll 9 documents have been written as of 2026-04-23.\n\n| # | Document | Status | Lines | Content |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 01 | Multi-Agent Overview | ✅ Done | 140 | Purpose, maturity, strategic direction |\n| 02 | Taxonomy and Inventory | ✅ Done | 177 | 4-layer model, agent classification, gaps |\n| 03 | Orchestration Architecture | ✅ Done | 194 | Routing, handoff contracts, escalation model |\n| 04 | Standard Workflows | ✅ Done | 267 | 5 canonical workflows with stages |\n| 05 | Agent Spec Framework | ✅ Done | 231 | Full template, migration strategy |\n| 06 | Governance and Operating Model | ✅ Done | 238 | Auth levels, escalation, lifecycle |\n| 07 | Metrics, KPIs and Adoption | ✅ Done | 271 | 4 metric categories, maturity model |\n| 08 | Gap Analysis and Roadmap | ✅ Done | 284 | 9 gaps, priority matrix, phased roadmap |\n| 09 | Case Studies | ✅ Done | 270 | 5 real case studies, template |\n\n**Total: 2,072 lines across 9 documents.**\n\n## Next step\n- Confluence publishing (requires Confluence space and page creation)"}]}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ejrxhjyqlp5p_2","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/docs/report-portal/index.html","edits":[{"oldText":"        <div class=\"report-grid\">\n          <article class=\"report-card featured\">\n            <p class=\"tag\">Week 4 Review</p>\n            <h3>OKR Progress Report — Start / W2 / W4</h3>\n            <p>Báo cáo đánh giá tiến độ OKR theo ba mốc, tổng hợp từ hệ Multi Agent và các repo AHV DTLX / QLHV.</p>\n            <div class=\"stats\">\n              <div><span>Checkpoint</span><strong>W4</strong></div>\n              <div><span>Objectives</span><strong>4</strong></div>\n              <div><span>Highlight</span><strong>O3, O4</strong></div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"actions\">\n              <a class=\"btn btn-primary\" href=\"./reports/okr-review-w4-2026-04/index.html\">Mở báo cáo</a>\n            </div>\n          </article>\n        </div>","newText":"        <div class=\"report-grid\">\n          <article class=\"report-card featured\">\n            <p