{"type":"message","id":"bf529d95","parentId":"4a31763e","timestamp":"2026-04-23T06:51:27.896Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to:\n1. Convert each of the 9 markdown files to HTML pages that are readable on the web\n2. Add them to the report portal with proper navigation\n3. Ensure download links work\n\nLet me create an HTML reader for each markdown file. I'll need to convert the markdown to HTML. Since there's no markdown parser available, I'll need to do a simple conversion or create HTML versions manually.\n\nActually, I can use Python's markdown library or create a simple converter. Let me check if there's a markdown library available.\n\nActually, the best approach would be to create a simple Python script that converts markdown to HTML, or create HTML versions directly. Since the markdown files are quite detailed, let me create a Python script to convert them to HTML pages.\n\n\nI'll start by trying to import the markdown module, and if that doesn't work, I'll write a simple converter to transform the markdown content into HTML.","thinkingSignature":"44477855d651cb2c22040e5afd2887dcfe19de7ba0dc4092ee956a754f91c73e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7bcjqryafbdn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\ntry:\n    import markdown\n    print('markdown-ok')\nexcept:\n    print('no-markdown')\ntry:\n    import misaka\n    print('misaka-ok')\nexcept:\n    print('no-misaka')\nPY","yieldMs":1000,"timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":146,"output":285,"cacheRead":138406,"cacheWrite":590,"totalTokens":139427,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776927078834,"responseId":"0638f4689e9030e446e083a2d4043982"}}
