{"type":"message","id":"83652c01","parentId":"d04788ad","timestamp":"2026-04-23T07:00:33.815Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update all the other documents that mention the agent count or the taxonomy, especially:1. 01-multi-agent-overview.md\n2. 08-gap-analysis-and-roadmap.md3. The multi-agent-governance-plan.md4. The HTML pages for docs 01 and 02\n\nLet me also update 01, 08 and plan doc.","thinkingSignature":"dfaa324be441014f4962fb5fc5615618dbae89d6a323d7f6b5b696e86f471341"},{"type":"text","text":"Cập nhật các tài liệu khác có liên quan.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b4694sluq3dy_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/docs/01-multi-agent-overview.md","edits":[{"oldText":"The ecosystem currently has <strong>65 agent/workspace</strong> in the system.","newText":"The ecosystem currently has <strong>65 agents</strong> (38 system/generic + 27 AHV DTLX project-specific)."}]}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b4694sluq3dy_2","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/docs/08-gap-analysis-and-roadmap.md","edits":[{"oldText":"### Observation 1 — Strong coverage\nThe ecosystem already covers most major internal operating functions needed for AI-assisted delivery.","newText":"### Observation 1 — Clear two-population structure\nThe ecosystem separates naturally into two populations: system/generic agents (38) and project-specific DTLX agents (27). This structure is intentional and should be preserved."}]}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b4694sluq3dy_3","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/docs/multi-agent-governance-plan.md","edits":[{"oldText":"1. **65 agents/workspace** — agent ecosystem","newText":"1. **65 agents total** — 38 system/generic + 27 DTLX project-specific agents"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":110,"output":443,"cacheRead":153869,"cacheWrite":3683,"totalTokens":158105,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776927622565,"responseId":"0638f688e8ee8ddd8fdec48d1816fd63"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e1004159","parentId":"83652c01","timestamp":"2026-04-23T07:00:33.876Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_b4694sluq3dy_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"edit\",\n  \"error\": \"Could not find the exact text in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/docs/01-multi-agent-overview.md. The old text must match exactly including all whitespace and newlines.\\nCurrent file contents:\\n# Multi-Agent Ecosystem Overview\\n\\n## Purpose\\nThis document defines the purpose, structure, and operating intent of the current multi-agent ecosystem. It is designed to serve as the top-level entry point for management and technical stakeholders before they review lower-level documentation such as taxonomy, workflows, governance, and metrics.\\n\\n## Executive Summary\\nThe current ecosystem is not a single assistant with ad hoc specialist prompts. It has evolved into a layered multi-agent operating model with clear evidence of specialization across product, engineering, quality, security, design, content, research, and operations.\\n\\nAt a high level, the ecosystem already demonstrates three important characteristics:\\n1. **Central orchestration exists** through a control layer centered around the m\\n... (truncated)\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"edit","error":"Could not find the exact text in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/docs/01-multi-agent-overview.md. The old text must match exactly including all whitespace and newlines.\nCurrent file contents:\n# Multi-Agent Ecosystem Overview\n\n## Purpose\nThis document defines the purpose, structure, and operating intent of the current multi-agent ecosystem. It is designed to serve as the top-level entry point for management and technical stakeholders before they review lower-level documentation such as taxonomy, workflows, governance, and metrics.\n\n## Executive Summary\nThe current ecosystem is not a single assistant with ad hoc specialist prompts. It has evolved into a layered multi-agent operating model with clear evidence of specialization across product, engineering, quality, security, design, content, research, and operations.\n\nAt a high level, the ecosystem already demonstrates three important characteristics:\n1. **Central orchestration exists** through a control layer centered around the m\n... (truncated)"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776927633870}}
{"type":"message","id":"c1a1da63","parentId":"e1004159","timestamp":"2026-04-23T07:00:33.898Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_b4694sluq3dy_2","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"edit\",\n  \"error\": \"Could not find the exact text in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/docs/08-gap-analysis-and-roadmap.md. The old text must match exactly including all whitespace and newlines.\\nCurrent file contents:\\n# Gap Analysis and Roadmap\\n\\n## Purpose\\nThis document identifies the gaps between the current state of the multi-agent ecosystem and the desired state of a mature, scalable, measurable agent platform. It provides the basis for prioritization and resource allocation.\\n\\n## Gap Analysis Framework\\nGaps are evaluated across four dimensions:\\n1. **Severity** — how much does this gap affect the ecosystem's reliability, quality, or scalability?\\n2. **Urgency** — how time-sensitive is addressing this gap?\\n3. **Effort** — how much work is required to address this gap?\\n4. **Impact** — how much value is created when the gap is closed?\\n\\nGaps are rated: Critical / High / Medium / Low\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Gap 1 — Inconsistent Agent Documentation Quality\\n\\n**Severity:** High\\n**Urgency:** High\\n**Effort:** Medium\\n**Impact:*\\n... (truncated)\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"edit","error":"Could not find the exact text in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/docs/08-gap-analysis-and-roadmap.md. The old text must match exactly including all whitespace and newlines.\nCurrent file contents:\n# Gap Analysis and Roadmap\n\n## Purpose\nThis document identifies the gaps between the current state of the multi-agent ecosystem and the desired state of a mature, scalable, measurable agent platform. It provides the basis for prioritization and resource allocation.\n\n## Gap Analysis Framework\nGaps are evaluated across four dimensions:\n1. **Severity** — how much does this gap affect the ecosystem's reliability, quality, or scalability?\n2. **Urgency** — how time-sensitive is addressing this gap?\n3. **Effort** — how much work is required to address this gap?\n4. **Impact** — how much value is created when the gap is closed?\n\nGaps are rated: Critical / High / Medium / Low\n\n---\n\n## Gap 1 — Inconsistent Agent Documentation Quality\n\n**Severity:** High\n**Urgency:** High\n**Effort:** Medium\n**Impact:*\n... (truncated)"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776927633888}}
{"type":"message","id":"a7dd8b3f","parentId":"c1a1da63","timestamp":"2026-04-23T07:00:33.915Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_b4694sluq3dy_3","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"edit\",\n  \"error\": \"Could not find the exact text in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/docs/multi-agent-governance-plan.md. The old text must match exactly including all whitespace and newlines.\\nCurrent file contents:\\n# Multi-Agent Ecosystem Documentation Plan\\n\\n## Scope\\nBuild a full, Confluence-ready documentation set for the current multi-agent ecosystem, including:\\n- inventory and taxonomy\\n- architecture and orchestration model\\n- standard workflows\\n- agent specification framework\\n- governance and escalation rules\\n- metrics and adoption measurement\\n- gap analysis and roadmap\\n- applied case studies\\n\\n## Current inventory snapshot\\n\\n### Observed ecosystem shape\\nThe current ecosystem is composed of two overlapping layers:\\n\\n1. **Generic reusable agents**\\n   - prompt-optimizer\\n   - planner\\n   - senior-frontend\\n   - senior-backend\\n   - senior-qa\\n   - senior-architect\\n   - senior-security\\n   - code-reviewer\\n   - clean-code\\n   - database-reviewer\\n   - database-schema-designer\\n   - content-engine\\n   - content-str\\n... (truncated)\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"edit","error":"Could not find the exact text in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/docs/multi-agent-governance-plan.md. The old text must match exactly including all whitespace and newlines.\nCurrent file contents:\n# Multi-Agent Ecosystem Documentation Plan\n\n## Scope\nBuild a full, Confluence-ready documentation set for the current multi-agent ecosystem, including:\n- inventory and taxonomy\n- architecture and orchestration model\n- standard workflows\n- agent specification framework\n- governance and escalation rules\n- metrics and adoption measurement\n- gap analysis and roadmap\n- applied case studies\n\n## Current inventory snapshot\n\n### Observed ecosystem shape\nThe current ecosystem is composed of two overlapping layers:\n\n1. **Generic reusable agents**\n   - prompt-optimizer\n   - planner\n   - senior-frontend\n   - senior-backend\n   - senior-qa\n   - senior-architect\n   - senior-security\n   - code-reviewer\n   - clean-code\n   - database-reviewer\n   - database-schema-designer\n   - content-engine\n   - content-str\n... (truncated)"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776927633909}}
{"type":"message","id":"d6b2854e","parentId":"a7dd8b3f","timestamp":"2026-04-23T07:00:49.814Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The files were reformatted. I need to rewrite the entire plan doc to match the new format. Let me rewrite it.","thinkingSignature":"fc6eac95b1994c86c03e14f12a1333b7714dfcb0cd8039a8b457b014cb597a8a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_u96cy9cb6c1q_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/docs/multi-agent-governance-plan.md","content":"# Multi-Agent Ecosystem Documentation Plan\n\n## Scope\nBuild a full, Confluence-ready documentation set for the current multi-agent ecosystem, including:\n- inventory and taxonomy\n- architecture and orchestration model\n- standard workflows\n- agent specification framework\n- governance and escalation rules\n- metrics and adoption measurement\n- gap analysis and roadmap\n- applied case studies\n\n## Current Ecosystem Composition\n\n**Total: 65 agents** across two distinct populations:\n\n- **System / Generic Agents: 38 agents** — reusable across any project\n- **AHV DTLX Project-Specific Sessions: 27 agents** — prefixed `ahv-dtlx-`, carrying project domain context\n\n### System agents (38):\nagile-product-owner, ai-seo, article-writing, clean-code, code-reviewer, coding-standards, content-engine, content-strategy, database-reviewer, database-schema-designer, deep-research, documentation-lookup, epic-design, harness-optimizer, market-intelligence, master-orchestrator, performance-optimizer, planner, playwright-pro, product-marketing-context, product-strategy, prompt-optimizer, realistic-seeder, refactor-cleaner, security-reviewer, senior-architect, senior-backend, senior-devops, senior-frontend, senior-qa, senior-security, seo-audit, shadcn-expert, stitch-design, stitch-loop, typescript-reviewer, ui-design-system, ui-ux-pro-max\n\n### DTLX project agents (27):\nahv-dtlx-agile, ahv-dtlx-architect, ahv-dtlx-be, ahv-dtlx-clean, ahv-dtlx-content-engine, ahv-dtlx-content-strategy, ahv-dtlx-db-schema, ahv-dtlx-devops, ahv-dtlx-docs, ahv-dtlx-epic, ahv-dtlx-fe, ahv-dtlx-harness, ahv-dtlx-market, ahv-dtlx-perf, ahv-dtlx-playwright, ahv-dtlx-product-strategy, ahv-dtlx-prompt, ahv-dtlx-qa, ahv-dtlx-review, ahv-dtlx-security, ahv-dtlx-senior-security, ahv-dtlx-seo, ahv-dtlx-shadcn, ahv-dtlx-standards, ahv-dtlx-stitch, ahv-dtlx-ui-design, ahv-dtlx-ui-ux\n\n## Document Completion Status\n\n| # | Document | Status | Content |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 01 | Multi-Agent Overview | ✅ Done | Purpose, maturity, strategic direction |\n| 02 | Taxonomy and Inventory | ✅ Done | 4-layer model, 65 agents classified (38+27), gaps |\n| 03 | Orchestration Architecture | ✅ Done | Routing, handoff contracts, escalation model |\n| 04 | Standard Workflows | ✅ Done | 5 canonical workflows with stages |\n| 05 | Agent Spec Framework | ✅ Done | Full template, migration strategy |\n| 06 | Governance and Operating Model | ✅ Done | Auth levels, escalation, lifecycle |\n| 07 | Metrics, KPIs and Adoption | ✅ Done | 4 metric categories, maturity model |\n| 08 | Gap Analysis and Roadmap | ✅ Done | 9 gaps, priority matrix, phased roadmap |\n| 09 | Case Studies | ✅ Done | 5 real case studies, template |\n\n**Total: 2,072 lines across 9 documents.**\n\n## Next Step\n- Confluence publishing (requires Confluence space and page creation)\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":829,"output":828,"cacheRead":155592,"cacheWrite":2454,"totalTokens":159703,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776927633922,"responseId":"0638f693786ee9e7fef99dfeab5e4fc0"}}
