iles—140 lines total could mean the first 136 lines are the overview, and the last few lines contain the gap analysis framework. But that doesn't quite make sense either, so let me reconsider what the actual file structure is showing me.\n\nActually, I think I've got it now: wc -l was reading both files in sequence (doc 01 with 140 lines, doc 08 with 284 lines), but the output got truncated to the first file's line count. So each file is separate, and what I'm seeing from offset 6 is definitely just doc 01's executive summary content.\n\nLooking at the actual file structure, doc 01 is definitely only 140 lines—it starts with the Executive Summary around line 6 and ends with the \"Definition of success\" section at line 136. But then when I read the same file starting from offset 6, I'm getting Gap Analysis content instead, which suggests the file might have been partially overwritten or there's some kind of read inconsistency happening.\n\nLet me just pull the complete files for both docs 01 and 08 so I can see exactly what's in them and fix the overlaps. I think the best approach is to rewrite both files completely to make sure the structure is clean and consistent throughout.","thinkingSignature":"5c727272d52693dfbd8853417cf4f32b87e058a333e94d5353d24fa33c7ec6dc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pfq0sxswuxqw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"wc -l /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/docs/01-multi-agent-overview.md /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/docs/08-gap-analysis-and-roadmap.md","yieldMs":1000,"timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1318,"output":754,"cacheRead":159688,"cacheWrite":499,"totalTokens":162259,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776927662858,"responseId":"0638f6b0ddfb2df6d5128a6e93b79f87"}}
