{"type":"compaction","id":"6662ce32","parentId":"c44b67f5","timestamp":"2026-04-23T07:55:00.889Z","summary":"## Goal\n1. Create professional Confluence documentation for project **AHV QLHV** based on the actual codebase.\n2. Create **OKR** for Khương Nịnh covering 4 Objectives (AHV Landing Page V2, CMS Trung tâm refactor, QLHV build from scratch, Multi AI Agent).\n3. Build **Multi-Agent Ecosystem Documentation Suite** (10 documents) for Confluence publishing.\n4. Create an **OKR Report Dashboard** (web-based, with PDF export) and a **Report Portal**.\n5. Expose SafeSight AI publicly via tunnel.\n6. Create a **Non-Tech User Guide** for the multi-agent system.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- User wants **professional, detailed** documentation based on real codebase.\n- OKR should be **chuyên nghiệp, học vấn cao** with KR sub-items.\n- Agent ecosystem docs should be **Confluence-ready** and published after review.\n- Report portal should support **reading on web + downloading** for each document.\n- User wants PDF export that **preserves colors and layout exactly** like the web version.\n- Non-tech guide should be written in Vietnamese, with detailed examples of good vs. bad requests.\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Confirmed SafeSight AI redirect issue: Next.js dev server blocking cross-origin for tunnel domains. Fixed by adding `allowedDevOrigins` in `next.config.ts` for `103.253.21.139` and `introductory-government-imagination-sept.trycloudflare.com`. Restarted dev server on port 3001. Public URL: `https://introductory-government-imagination-sept.trycloudflare.com`\n- [x] Created comprehensive **OKR** for Khương Nịnh with 4 Objectives:\n  - **O1**: AHV Landing Page V2 (production, maintain + enhance)\n  - **O2**: AHV DTLX CMS Trung tâm (refactor, optimize, architecture migration, frontend redesign)\n  - **O3**: AHV DTLX → QLHV (CMS thầy giáo) — build new FE + BE from scratch\n  - **O4**: Multi AI Agent — research, trial, integrate into team workflow\n- [x] OKR written with **professional Vietnamese language**, each KR has **sub-items** (KR con / chỉ dấu thực thi) and expected outcomes\n- [x] Inventory of **65 agents** across two populations: **38 system/generic** + **27 DTLX project-specific** (prefix `ahv-dtlx-`)\n- [x] Collected evidence from repos for scoring:\n  - FE: Start=20 commits, W2=103 commits, W4=122 commits\n  - BE: Start=29 commits, W2=93 commits, W4=155 commits\n  - Commit tags show: import, finance, exam, support request, RBAC, teacher isolation, CI/CD, swagger 18 modules/100+ endpoints\n- [x] Created **OKR W4 assessment report** with Start/W2/W4 scoring for all 4 Objectives and 20 KRs\n- [x] Built **OKR report dashboard** at `docs/okr-report/` — HTML+CSS, running on `http://103.253.21.139:8787`\n- [x] Added **PDF export button** to OKR report using CSS `@media print` + `window.print()` (preserves dark theme colors)\n- [x] Created **Report Portal** at `docs/report-portal/` with:\n  - Portal home listing all reports\n  - OKR W4 report page\n  - Multi-Agent Governance docs page\n  - Running on `http://103.253.21.139:8790`\n- [x] Built complete **10-document Multi-Agent Governance Suite**:\n  - `01-multi-agent-overview.md` (140 lines)\n  - `02-agent-taxonomy-and-inventory.md` (177 lines) — 65 agents: 38 system + 27 DTLX\n  - `03-orchestration-architecture.md` (194 lines)\n  - `04-standard-workflows.md` (267 lines) — 5 canonical workflows\n  - `05-agent-spec-framework.md` (231 lines)\n  - `06-governance-and-operating-model.md` (238 lines)\n  - `07-metrics-kpis-and-adoption.md` (271 lines)\n  - `08-gap-analysis-and-roadmap.md` (284 lines) — 9 gaps, 3-phase roadmap\n  - `09-case-studies.md` (270 lines) — 5 real case studies\n  - **`10-non-tech-guide.md`** — Full usage guide for non-technical users, 14,465 bytes\n  - Total: **10 documents** across the full suite\n- [x] Corrected agent counts: **38 system/generic** + **27 DTLX project-specific** (not ~40 total as user initially stated)\n- [x] Built **Python markdown-to-HTML converter** (`docs/md2html.py`) to render all MD files as readable HTML pages\n- [x] Regenerated all HTML pages for the portal including the new non-tech guide\n- [x] Updated portal hub to show: **38 system agents + 27 DTLX agents**, with per-document **\"📖 Đọc trên web\"** and **\"⬇️ Tải .md\"** buttons\n- [x] Created **Non-Tech User Guide** (`10-non-tech-guide.md`) with 10 sections: what the system is, capabilities, how to make effective requests, types of suitable requests, basic workflow, important notes, how to read/use results, when to use vs not use, real-world use cases (5 scenarios), glossary of terms\n- [x] Converted non-tech guide to HTML and added to portal with a highlighted \"For Everyone\" card\n- [x] Updated `multi-agent-governance-plan.md` to reflect 10 documents total\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **Publish governance docs to Confluence** — awaiting user review confirmation\n- [ ] **VPS bot activation** on `161.248.81.141` with credential `m-@955nhAJ3lJK` — user asked but hasn't provided SSH username or bot name yet\n\n### Blocked\n- Cannot install Chromium on the current session due to `elevated` tool gate restriction (runtime=direct). PDF export uses `window.print()` CSS approach instead.\n- VPS bot activation requires SSH username and bot/service name — not yet provided by user.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **4 Objectives instead of 3**: User confirmed splitting AHV DTLX into 2 separate projects (CMS Trung tâm vs QLHV) warrants 2 separate Objectives.\n- **Start/W2/W4 scoring**: User clarified W4 = current checkpoint (4 weeks elapsed), with Start and W2 being prior milestones.\n- **HTML portal over Vercel for now**: User chose Option B (website), not GitLab/Vercel yet. Created static portal with local servers.\n- **2 agent populations**: 38 system/generic + 27 DTLX project-specific (prefix `ahv-dtlx-`). These are project sessions with domain context, not part of the reusable platform.\n- **CSS print-to-PDF approach**: Since Chromium couldn't be installed, used `@media print` CSS to preserve dark theme colors in PDF output via browser's native print-to-PDF.\n- **Non-tech guide as separate document**: Created standalone `10-non-tech-guide.md` with distinct \"For Everyone\" branding and highlighted placement on the portal hub.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Await user review** of the 10 governance documents (currently accessible on web portal)\n2. **Publish governance docs to Confluence** once user confirms review is complete\n3. **Resolve VPS bot activation**: Need SSH username and bot/service name from user for `161.248.81.141`\n4. **Vercel/GitLab deployment**: User chose Option B (website portal) but hasn't committed to GitLab group name or Vercel project setup yet\n5. **PDF perfection**: If user needs true pixel-perfect colored PDF, need to install Chromium headless separately\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Report Portal URL**: `http://103.253.21.139:8790`\n- **OKR Report URL**: `http://103.253.21.139:8790/reports/okr-review-w4-2026-04/index.html`\n- **Multi-Agent Docs Hub**: `http://103.253.21.139:8790/reports/multi-agent-governance/index.html`\n- **Non-Tech User Guide**: `http://103.253.21.139:8790/reports/multi-agent-governance/10-non-tech-guide.html`\n- **All 10 governance docs**: `docs/report-portal/reports/multi-agent-governance/` (HTML readable + MD downloadable)\n- **Original MD source files**: `docs/01-multi-agent-overview.md` through `docs/10-non-tech-guide.md`\n- **Non-tech guide source**: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/docs/10-non-tech-guide.md` (14,465 bytes)\n- **SafeSight AI public**: `https://introductory-government-imagination-sept.trycloudflare.com`\n- **VPS bot IP**: `161.248.81.141` / credential: `m-@955nhAJ3lJK`\n- **AHV QLHV repos**: FE `/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe`, BE `/projects/ahv-qlhv-be`\n- **Confluence space AHVTEACHER** pages still exist from earlier work (obsolete CMS Teacher pages not yet deleted)\n\n<read-files>\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-