{"type":"message","id":"14271e44","parentId":"1d0d5f84","timestamp":"2026-04-23T08:35:52.108Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So we have:\n- Node.js v8 module ✓\n- Pillow (PIL) ✓\n- No playwright, selenium, pyppeteer, imgkit, weasyprint, or wkhtmltopdf\n\nLet me try a completely different approach. I can use Node.js to:\n1. Load the mermaid library\n2. Use a virtual DOM (like jsdom) to create a browser-like environment\n3. Render the mermaid diagrams\n\nOr, I can use the `mermaid` library's API directly with Node.js.\n\nLet me try installing `jsdom` and using mermaid with it.","thinkingSignature":"ee412e5c60e2b5e1b72baf1b451873f120913680378413472910740cb53de85d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_53bslc3osj7d_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/mermaid_render && npm install jsdom 2>&1 | tail -3 && echo \"done\"","yieldMs":30000,"timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":87,"output":197,"cacheRead":51667,"cacheWrite":689,"totalTokens":52640,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776933345299,"responseId":"06390ce2b35373a50f91e4c8c953477d"}}
