{"type":"message","id":"5da74385","parentId":"7084f746","timestamp":"2026-04-23T08:36:56.298Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see that mermaid exports a `render` function that takes a container element and renders to it. The issue is that it needs a DOM with SVG support.\n\nLet me try a different approach. I'll use Node.js with the `--experimental-vm-modules` flag and write a proper ESM script that imports mermaid and renders it using a virtual DOM.\n\nActually, looking at the mermaid code, it uses D3 for SVG rendering. This requires a full DOM with SVG support. JSDOM doesn't have great SVG support.\n\nLet me try using the Python `pillow` library to draw diagrams programmatically, OR I can try to use a simpler approach - write a Node.js script that:\n\n\n- Loads mermaid\n- Uses JSDOM with SVG support\n- Renders to SVG\n\nOr even simpler - let me try to use Python's `svgelement` or similar to render SVG. Actually, let me try a completely different approach. Since the machine has Node.js and mermaid is an npm package, let me write a proper ESM script using Node.js's native ESM support.\n\nWriting ESM script...","thinkingSignature":"322f60343df3c9a9b6d37584d2e792e14ad075016c7ad449b301a8594ad1409d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xnmtdk7a8bu9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try Node.js native ESM with --experimental-vm-modules for SVG rendering\ncd /tmp/mermaid_render && cat > render-esm.mjs << 'SCRIPT'\nimport { readFileSync } from 'fs';\nimport { JSDOM } from 'jsdom';\n\n// Load mermaid\nconst mermaidCode = readFileSync('./node_modules/mermaid/dist/mermaid.esm.min.mjs', 'utf8');\n\nconst html = `<!DOCTYPE html><html><body><div id=\"app\"></div></body></html>`;\nconst dom = new JSDOM(html, { runScripts: 'dangerously', pretendToBeVisual: true });\nconst { window } = dom;\nconst { document } = window;\n\n// Inject mermaid as a global\nconst script = document.createElement('script');\nscript.textContent = mermaidCode;\ndocument.head.appendChild(script);\n\nawait new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000));\n\nconst mermaid = window.mermaid || window.Sc;\nconsole.log('mermaid:', typeof mermaid);\nconsole.log('window keys with mermaid:', Object.keys(window).filter(k => k.toLowerCase().includes('mera')));\n\ndom.window.close();\nSCRIPT\ntimeout 15 node --experimental-vm-modules render-esm.mjs 2>&1 | head -20","yieldMs":15000,"timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":2418,"output":544,"cacheRead":53207,"cacheWrite":937,"totalTokens":57106,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776933399332,"responseId":"06390d18dbae68c862753db0e857ca25"}}
