{"type":"message","id":"30f834e8","parentId":"198f1911","timestamp":"2026-04-23T09:25:34.020Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants each Key Result to have a specific start date (when the requirement was received). So each KR should have its own start date, not just the overall Objective start date.\n\nI need to determine appropriate start dates for each of the 5 KRs. Since the overall OKR period started 03/04/2026, each KR would have been kicked off at different times. But I don't have exact data for each KR's start date.\n\nLet me think about this practically:\n- KR1 (Refactor modules) - this would logically start at the beginning since refactoring is foundational\n- KR2 (Optimize bottlenecks) - this could start after initial assessment, maybe W1-W2\n\n\n- KR3 (Architecture migration) - this is more strategic, might start slightly later\n- KR4 (Redesign frontend) - UI work might start after architecture is clearer\n- KR5 (Quality control) - this runs parallel throughout\n\nSince the user mentioned W4 checkpoint is \"current\" (2026-04-23), and W2 was reviewed earlier, the OKR period started around 03/04/2026. For the specific KR start dates, I should use reasonable assumptions based on when each would naturally begin in a typical refactoring workflow, or ask the user for the exact dates they have in mind.\n\nActually, thinking about this more carefully—the user said \"ngày bắt đầu thực hiện (lúc nhận yêu cầu)\" which means the start date when the requirement was received. Since these KRs are sequential phases of the overall refactoring work, they likely started at different points:\n- KR1 likely started first around 03/04/2026\n- KR2 started when bottlenecks were identified, maybe 1 week later\n- KR3 started when architecture was defined, maybe W2\n- KR4 started when redesign priorities were set\n- KR5 has been ongoing throughout\n\nBut without more specific information from the user, I should present reasonable es